==Short Description==

Smart Containers Group is an established Swiss-based company holding that has been operational for five years and comprises two operating companies, namely Sky Cell and Food Guardians. The Group aims to disrupt the logistics sector by using their self-developed, temperature-controlled containers for sensitive pharmaceutical and food products across the supply chain. The containers are equipped with a newly developed and patented insulation technology. This cutting-edge hardware is further combined with technology solutions that enables the creation of a logistic ecosystem backed by the blockchain technology. They call it LOGI CHAIN with its own ERC-20 token LOGI Tokens that is used for payments in the LOGI CHAIN ecosystem. It addresses the current inefficient paper trail in logistics according to which an international shipment of a container calls for hundred of documents. Smart Containers have in mind to move this paper trail of the container onto blockchains. Public documents can be recorded on the Ethereum blockchain while confidential data and documents will be placed on a permissioned blockchain. An open source reader enables access to the corresponding documents for the various stakeholders of a shipment that they are able to process the relevant actions. Furthermore the integration of Smart Contracts in the process will automate the invoicing and payment process. Due to the sensors installed in the containers, its location can be determined at any time and even the container recognizes itself when a shipment has arrived at its destination and when its contents have been unloaded. Payments can therefore be executed instantaneously when the container is unloaded. <ref name="Whitepaper"/> <ref>https://masterthecrypto.com/smartcontainers-ico-review-smartcontainers-ico-analysis/, access 07/05/18.</ref>


