==Funding==
Smart Containers ICO for both of the tokens took place on June 7 2018 and ended on June 30 the same year.
* SMARC: One SMARC token could be purchased for $0.4320. All in all, SMARC tokens of $36M could be sold. Most of these funds will be used primarily for the further development of the two sub-companies, Food Guardians ($13M) and SkyCells ($15M). SMARC is a profit-sharing token offering 20% of future dividends as well as any exit profits from subdivisions paid out in ETH (proportionally to tokens in circulation). The total supply of SMARC tokens is 150M with 120M available for the ICO.
* LOGI: The LOGI coin is used to fuel the payment of smart contract transactions in the LOGI ecosystem. 20M tokens were available for the ICO. The hard cap was $4M. Most of these funds will be used for the development to date and for the foundation, which always strives to ensure that everything runs smoothly. <ref>https://cryptowithoutborders.com/tag/logi/, access 07/13/18.</ref><ref name="Whitepaper"/>


